module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginSslProtocols

-- | A complex type that contains information about the SSL/TLS protocols
--   that CloudFront can use when establishing an HTTPS connection with
--   your origin.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOriginSslProtocols</a> smart constructor.
data OriginSslProtocols
OriginSslProtocols' :: Int -> [SslProtocol] -> OriginSslProtocols

-- | The number of SSL/TLS protocols that you want to allow CloudFront to
--   use when establishing an HTTPS connection with this origin.
[$sel:quantity:OriginSslProtocols'] :: OriginSslProtocols -> Int

-- | A list that contains allowed SSL/TLS protocols for this distribution.
[$sel:items:OriginSslProtocols'] :: OriginSslProtocols -> [SslProtocol]

-- | Create a value of <a>OriginSslProtocols</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:quantity:OriginSslProtocols'</a>,
--   <a>originSslProtocols_quantity</a> - The number of SSL/TLS protocols
--   that you want to allow CloudFront to use when establishing an HTTPS
--   connection with this origin.
--   
--   <a>$sel:items:OriginSslProtocols'</a>, <a>originSslProtocols_items</a>
--   - A list that contains allowed SSL/TLS protocols for this
--   distribution.
newOriginSslProtocols :: Int -> OriginSslProtocols

-- | The number of SSL/TLS protocols that you want to allow CloudFront to
--   use when establishing an HTTPS connection with this origin.
originSslProtocols_quantity :: Lens' OriginSslProtocols Int

-- | A list that contains allowed SSL/TLS protocols for this distribution.
originSslProtocols_items :: Lens' OriginSslProtocols [SslProtocol]
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginSslProtocols.OriginSslProtocols
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginSslProtocols.OriginSslProtocols
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginSslProtocols.OriginSslProtocols
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginSslProtocols.OriginSslProtocols
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginSslProtocols.OriginSslProtocols
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginSslProtocols.OriginSslProtocols
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginSslProtocols.OriginSslProtocols
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.ToXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginSslProtocols.OriginSslProtocols


module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.CustomOriginConfig

-- | A custom origin. A custom origin is any origin that is <i>not</i> an
--   Amazon S3 bucket, with one exception. An Amazon S3 bucket that is
--   <a>configured with static website hosting</a> <i>is</i> a custom
--   origin.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newCustomOriginConfig</a> smart constructor.
data CustomOriginConfig
CustomOriginConfig' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe OriginSslProtocols -> Int -> Int -> OriginProtocolPolicy -> CustomOriginConfig

-- | Specifies how long, in seconds, CloudFront persists its connection to
--   the origin. The minimum timeout is 1 second, the maximum is 60
--   seconds, and the default (if you don’t specify otherwise) is 5
--   seconds.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Keep-alive Timeout</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:originKeepaliveTimeout:CustomOriginConfig'] :: CustomOriginConfig -> Maybe Int

-- | Specifies how long, in seconds, CloudFront waits for a response from
--   the origin. This is also known as the <i>origin response timeout</i>.
--   The minimum timeout is 1 second, the maximum is 60 seconds, and the
--   default (if you don’t specify otherwise) is 30 seconds.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Response Timeout</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:originReadTimeout:CustomOriginConfig'] :: CustomOriginConfig -> Maybe Int

-- | Specifies the minimum SSL/TLS protocol that CloudFront uses when
--   connecting to your origin over HTTPS. Valid values include
--   <tt>SSLv3</tt>, <tt>TLSv1</tt>, <tt>TLSv1.1</tt>, and
--   <tt>TLSv1.2</tt>.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Minimum Origin SSL Protocol</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:originSslProtocols:CustomOriginConfig'] :: CustomOriginConfig -> Maybe OriginSslProtocols

-- | The HTTP port that CloudFront uses to connect to the origin. Specify
--   the HTTP port that the origin listens on.
[$sel:hTTPPort:CustomOriginConfig'] :: CustomOriginConfig -> Int

-- | The HTTPS port that CloudFront uses to connect to the origin. Specify
--   the HTTPS port that the origin listens on.
[$sel:hTTPSPort:CustomOriginConfig'] :: CustomOriginConfig -> Int

-- | Specifies the protocol (HTTP or HTTPS) that CloudFront uses to connect
--   to the origin. Valid values are:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>http-only</tt> – CloudFront always uses HTTP to connect to the
--   origin.</li>
--   <li><tt>match-viewer</tt> – CloudFront connects to the origin using
--   the same protocol that the viewer used to connect to CloudFront.</li>
--   <li><tt>https-only</tt> – CloudFront always uses HTTPS to connect to
--   the origin.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:originProtocolPolicy:CustomOriginConfig'] :: CustomOriginConfig -> OriginProtocolPolicy

-- | Create a value of <a>CustomOriginConfig</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:originKeepaliveTimeout:CustomOriginConfig'</a>,
--   <a>customOriginConfig_originKeepaliveTimeout</a> - Specifies how long,
--   in seconds, CloudFront persists its connection to the origin. The
--   minimum timeout is 1 second, the maximum is 60 seconds, and the
--   default (if you don’t specify otherwise) is 5 seconds.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Keep-alive Timeout</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:originReadTimeout:CustomOriginConfig'</a>,
--   <a>customOriginConfig_originReadTimeout</a> - Specifies how long, in
--   seconds, CloudFront waits for a response from the origin. This is also
--   known as the <i>origin response timeout</i>. The minimum timeout is 1
--   second, the maximum is 60 seconds, and the default (if you don’t
--   specify otherwise) is 30 seconds.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Response Timeout</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:originSslProtocols:CustomOriginConfig'</a>,
--   <a>customOriginConfig_originSslProtocols</a> - Specifies the minimum
--   SSL/TLS protocol that CloudFront uses when connecting to your origin
--   over HTTPS. Valid values include <tt>SSLv3</tt>, <tt>TLSv1</tt>,
--   <tt>TLSv1.1</tt>, and <tt>TLSv1.2</tt>.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Minimum Origin SSL Protocol</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:hTTPPort:CustomOriginConfig'</a>,
--   <a>customOriginConfig_hTTPPort</a> - The HTTP port that CloudFront
--   uses to connect to the origin. Specify the HTTP port that the origin
--   listens on.
--   
--   <a>$sel:hTTPSPort:CustomOriginConfig'</a>,
--   <a>customOriginConfig_hTTPSPort</a> - The HTTPS port that CloudFront
--   uses to connect to the origin. Specify the HTTPS port that the origin
--   listens on.
--   
--   <a>$sel:originProtocolPolicy:CustomOriginConfig'</a>,
--   <a>customOriginConfig_originProtocolPolicy</a> - Specifies the
--   protocol (HTTP or HTTPS) that CloudFront uses to connect to the
--   origin. Valid values are:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>http-only</tt> – CloudFront always uses HTTP to connect to the
--   origin.</li>
--   <li><tt>match-viewer</tt> – CloudFront connects to the origin using
--   the same protocol that the viewer used to connect to CloudFront.</li>
--   <li><tt>https-only</tt> – CloudFront always uses HTTPS to connect to
--   the origin.</li>
--   </ul>
newCustomOriginConfig :: Int -> Int -> OriginProtocolPolicy -> CustomOriginConfig

-- | Specifies how long, in seconds, CloudFront persists its connection to
--   the origin. The minimum timeout is 1 second, the maximum is 60
--   seconds, and the default (if you don’t specify otherwise) is 5
--   seconds.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Keep-alive Timeout</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
customOriginConfig_originKeepaliveTimeout :: Lens' CustomOriginConfig (Maybe Int)

-- | Specifies how long, in seconds, CloudFront waits for a response from
--   the origin. This is also known as the <i>origin response timeout</i>.
--   The minimum timeout is 1 second, the maximum is 60 seconds, and the
--   default (if you don’t specify otherwise) is 30 seconds.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Response Timeout</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
customOriginConfig_originReadTimeout :: Lens' CustomOriginConfig (Maybe Int)

-- | Specifies the minimum SSL/TLS protocol that CloudFront uses when
--   connecting to your origin over HTTPS. Valid values include
--   <tt>SSLv3</tt>, <tt>TLSv1</tt>, <tt>TLSv1.1</tt>, and
--   <tt>TLSv1.2</tt>.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Minimum Origin SSL Protocol</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
customOriginConfig_originSslProtocols :: Lens' CustomOriginConfig (Maybe OriginSslProtocols)

-- | The HTTP port that CloudFront uses to connect to the origin. Specify
--   the HTTP port that the origin listens on.
customOriginConfig_hTTPPort :: Lens' CustomOriginConfig Int

-- | The HTTPS port that CloudFront uses to connect to the origin. Specify
--   the HTTPS port that the origin listens on.
customOriginConfig_hTTPSPort :: Lens' CustomOriginConfig Int

-- | Specifies the protocol (HTTP or HTTPS) that CloudFront uses to connect
--   to the origin. Valid values are:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>http-only</tt> – CloudFront always uses HTTP to connect to the
--   origin.</li>
--   <li><tt>match-viewer</tt> – CloudFront connects to the origin using
--   the same protocol that the viewer used to connect to CloudFront.</li>
--   <li><tt>https-only</tt> – CloudFront always uses HTTPS to connect to
--   the origin.</li>
--   </ul>
customOriginConfig_originProtocolPolicy :: Lens' CustomOriginConfig OriginProtocolPolicy
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.CustomOriginConfig.CustomOriginConfig
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.CustomOriginConfig.CustomOriginConfig
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.CustomOriginConfig.CustomOriginConfig
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.CustomOriginConfig.CustomOriginConfig
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.CustomOriginConfig.CustomOriginConfig
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.CustomOriginConfig.CustomOriginConfig
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.CustomOriginConfig.CustomOriginConfig
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.ToXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.CustomOriginConfig.CustomOriginConfig


module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origin

-- | An origin.
--   
--   An origin is the location where content is stored, and from which
--   CloudFront gets content to serve to viewers. To specify an origin:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Use <tt>S3OriginConfig</tt> to specify an Amazon S3 bucket that is
--   not configured with static website hosting.</li>
--   <li>Use <tt>CustomOriginConfig</tt> to specify all other kinds of
--   origins, including:<ul><li>An Amazon S3 bucket that is configured with
--   static website hosting</li><li>An Elastic Load Balancing load
--   balancer</li><li>An AWS Elemental MediaPackage endpoint</li><li>An AWS
--   Elemental MediaStore container</li><li>Any other HTTP server, running
--   on an Amazon EC2 instance or any other kind of host</li></ul></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For the current maximum number of origins that you can specify per
--   distribution, see <a>General Quotas on Web Distributions</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i> (quotas were formerly
--   referred to as limits).
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOrigin</a> smart constructor.
data Origin
Origin' :: Maybe CustomHeaders -> Maybe CustomOriginConfig -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe S3OriginConfig -> Maybe Text -> Maybe OriginShield -> Text -> Text -> Origin

-- | A list of HTTP header names and values that CloudFront adds to the
--   requests that it sends to the origin.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Adding Custom Headers to Origin
--   Requests</a> in the <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:customHeaders:Origin'] :: Origin -> Maybe CustomHeaders

-- | Use this type to specify an origin that is not an Amazon S3 bucket,
--   with one exception. If the Amazon S3 bucket is configured with static
--   website hosting, use this type. If the Amazon S3 bucket is not
--   configured with static website hosting, use the
--   <tt>S3OriginConfig</tt> type instead.
[$sel:customOriginConfig:Origin'] :: Origin -> Maybe CustomOriginConfig

-- | The number of seconds that CloudFront waits when trying to establish a
--   connection to the origin. The minimum timeout is 1 second, the maximum
--   is 10 seconds, and the default (if you don’t specify otherwise) is 10
--   seconds.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Connection Timeout</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:connectionTimeout:Origin'] :: Origin -> Maybe Int

-- | The number of times that CloudFront attempts to connect to the origin.
--   The minimum number is 1, the maximum is 3, and the default (if you
--   don’t specify otherwise) is 3.
--   
--   For a custom origin (including an Amazon S3 bucket that’s configured
--   with static website hosting), this value also specifies the number of
--   times that CloudFront attempts to get a response from the origin, in
--   the case of an <a>Origin Response Timeout</a>.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Connection Attempts</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:connectionAttempts:Origin'] :: Origin -> Maybe Int

-- | Use this type to specify an origin that is an Amazon S3 bucket that is
--   not configured with static website hosting. To specify any other type
--   of origin, including an Amazon S3 bucket that is configured with
--   static website hosting, use the <tt>CustomOriginConfig</tt> type
--   instead.
[$sel:s3OriginConfig:Origin'] :: Origin -> Maybe S3OriginConfig

-- | An optional path that CloudFront appends to the origin domain name
--   when CloudFront requests content from the origin.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Path</a> in the <i>Amazon
--   CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:originPath:Origin'] :: Origin -> Maybe Text

-- | CloudFront Origin Shield. Using Origin Shield can help reduce the load
--   on your origin.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Using Origin Shield</a> in the <i>Amazon
--   CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:originShield:Origin'] :: Origin -> Maybe OriginShield

-- | A unique identifier for the origin. This value must be unique within
--   the distribution.
--   
--   Use this value to specify the <tt>TargetOriginId</tt> in a
--   <tt>CacheBehavior</tt> or <tt>DefaultCacheBehavior</tt>.
[$sel:id:Origin'] :: Origin -> Text

-- | The domain name for the origin.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Domain Name</a> in the <i>Amazon
--   CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:domainName:Origin'] :: Origin -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>Origin</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:customHeaders:Origin'</a>, <a>origin_customHeaders</a> - A
--   list of HTTP header names and values that CloudFront adds to the
--   requests that it sends to the origin.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Adding Custom Headers to Origin
--   Requests</a> in the <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customOriginConfig:Origin'</a>,
--   <a>origin_customOriginConfig</a> - Use this type to specify an origin
--   that is not an Amazon S3 bucket, with one exception. If the Amazon S3
--   bucket is configured with static website hosting, use this type. If
--   the Amazon S3 bucket is not configured with static website hosting,
--   use the <tt>S3OriginConfig</tt> type instead.
--   
--   <a>$sel:connectionTimeout:Origin'</a>, <a>origin_connectionTimeout</a>
--   - The number of seconds that CloudFront waits when trying to establish
--   a connection to the origin. The minimum timeout is 1 second, the
--   maximum is 10 seconds, and the default (if you don’t specify
--   otherwise) is 10 seconds.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Connection Timeout</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:connectionAttempts:Origin'</a>,
--   <a>origin_connectionAttempts</a> - The number of times that CloudFront
--   attempts to connect to the origin. The minimum number is 1, the
--   maximum is 3, and the default (if you don’t specify otherwise) is 3.
--   
--   For a custom origin (including an Amazon S3 bucket that’s configured
--   with static website hosting), this value also specifies the number of
--   times that CloudFront attempts to get a response from the origin, in
--   the case of an <a>Origin Response Timeout</a>.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Connection Attempts</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:s3OriginConfig:Origin'</a>, <a>origin_s3OriginConfig</a> - Use
--   this type to specify an origin that is an Amazon S3 bucket that is not
--   configured with static website hosting. To specify any other type of
--   origin, including an Amazon S3 bucket that is configured with static
--   website hosting, use the <tt>CustomOriginConfig</tt> type instead.
--   
--   <a>$sel:originPath:Origin'</a>, <a>origin_originPath</a> - An optional
--   path that CloudFront appends to the origin domain name when CloudFront
--   requests content from the origin.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Path</a> in the <i>Amazon
--   CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:originShield:Origin'</a>, <a>origin_originShield</a> -
--   CloudFront Origin Shield. Using Origin Shield can help reduce the load
--   on your origin.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Using Origin Shield</a> in the <i>Amazon
--   CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:id:Origin'</a>, <a>origin_id</a> - A unique identifier for the
--   origin. This value must be unique within the distribution.
--   
--   Use this value to specify the <tt>TargetOriginId</tt> in a
--   <tt>CacheBehavior</tt> or <tt>DefaultCacheBehavior</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domainName:Origin'</a>, <a>origin_domainName</a> - The domain
--   name for the origin.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Domain Name</a> in the <i>Amazon
--   CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
newOrigin :: Text -> Text -> Origin

-- | A list of HTTP header names and values that CloudFront adds to the
--   requests that it sends to the origin.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Adding Custom Headers to Origin
--   Requests</a> in the <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
origin_customHeaders :: Lens' Origin (Maybe CustomHeaders)

-- | Use this type to specify an origin that is not an Amazon S3 bucket,
--   with one exception. If the Amazon S3 bucket is configured with static
--   website hosting, use this type. If the Amazon S3 bucket is not
--   configured with static website hosting, use the
--   <tt>S3OriginConfig</tt> type instead.
origin_customOriginConfig :: Lens' Origin (Maybe CustomOriginConfig)

-- | The number of seconds that CloudFront waits when trying to establish a
--   connection to the origin. The minimum timeout is 1 second, the maximum
--   is 10 seconds, and the default (if you don’t specify otherwise) is 10
--   seconds.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Connection Timeout</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
origin_connectionTimeout :: Lens' Origin (Maybe Int)

-- | The number of times that CloudFront attempts to connect to the origin.
--   The minimum number is 1, the maximum is 3, and the default (if you
--   don’t specify otherwise) is 3.
--   
--   For a custom origin (including an Amazon S3 bucket that’s configured
--   with static website hosting), this value also specifies the number of
--   times that CloudFront attempts to get a response from the origin, in
--   the case of an <a>Origin Response Timeout</a>.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Connection Attempts</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
origin_connectionAttempts :: Lens' Origin (Maybe Int)

-- | Use this type to specify an origin that is an Amazon S3 bucket that is
--   not configured with static website hosting. To specify any other type
--   of origin, including an Amazon S3 bucket that is configured with
--   static website hosting, use the <tt>CustomOriginConfig</tt> type
--   instead.
origin_s3OriginConfig :: Lens' Origin (Maybe S3OriginConfig)

-- | An optional path that CloudFront appends to the origin domain name
--   when CloudFront requests content from the origin.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Path</a> in the <i>Amazon
--   CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
origin_originPath :: Lens' Origin (Maybe Text)

-- | CloudFront Origin Shield. Using Origin Shield can help reduce the load
--   on your origin.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Using Origin Shield</a> in the <i>Amazon
--   CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
origin_originShield :: Lens' Origin (Maybe OriginShield)

-- | A unique identifier for the origin. This value must be unique within
--   the distribution.
--   
--   Use this value to specify the <tt>TargetOriginId</tt> in a
--   <tt>CacheBehavior</tt> or <tt>DefaultCacheBehavior</tt>.
origin_id :: Lens' Origin Text

-- | The domain name for the origin.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Origin Domain Name</a> in the <i>Amazon
--   CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
origin_domainName :: Lens' Origin Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origin.Origin
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origin.Origin
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origin.Origin
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origin.Origin
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origin.Origin
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origin.Origin
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origin.Origin
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.ToXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origin.Origin


module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origins

-- | Contains information about the origins for this distribution.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOrigins</a> smart constructor.
data Origins
Origins' :: Int -> NonEmpty Origin -> Origins

-- | The number of origins for this distribution.
[$sel:quantity:Origins'] :: Origins -> Int

-- | A list of origins.
[$sel:items:Origins'] :: Origins -> NonEmpty Origin

-- | Create a value of <a>Origins</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:quantity:Origins'</a>, <a>origins_quantity</a> - The number of
--   origins for this distribution.
--   
--   <a>$sel:items:Origins'</a>, <a>origins_items</a> - A list of origins.
newOrigins :: Int -> NonEmpty Origin -> Origins

-- | The number of origins for this distribution.
origins_quantity :: Lens' Origins Int

-- | A list of origins.
origins_items :: Lens' Origins (NonEmpty Origin)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origins.Origins
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origins.Origins
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origins.Origins
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origins.Origins
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origins.Origins
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origins.Origins

instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.ToXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Origins.Origins


module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StatusCodes

-- | A complex data type for the status codes that you specify that, when
--   returned by a primary origin, trigger CloudFront to failover to a
--   second origin.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newStatusCodes</a> smart constructor.
data StatusCodes
StatusCodes' :: Int -> NonEmpty Int -> StatusCodes

-- | The number of status codes.
[$sel:quantity:StatusCodes'] :: StatusCodes -> Int

-- | The items (status codes) for an origin group.
[$sel:items:StatusCodes'] :: StatusCodes -> NonEmpty Int

-- | Create a value of <a>StatusCodes</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:quantity:StatusCodes'</a>, <a>statusCodes_quantity</a> - The
--   number of status codes.
--   
--   <a>$sel:items:StatusCodes'</a>, <a>statusCodes_items</a> - The items
--   (status codes) for an origin group.
newStatusCodes :: Int -> NonEmpty Int -> StatusCodes

-- | The number of status codes.
statusCodes_quantity :: Lens' StatusCodes Int

-- | The items (status codes) for an origin group.
statusCodes_items :: Lens' StatusCodes (NonEmpty Int)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StatusCodes.StatusCodes
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StatusCodes.StatusCodes
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StatusCodes.StatusCodes
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StatusCodes.StatusCodes
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StatusCodes.StatusCodes
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StatusCodes.StatusCodes
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StatusCodes.StatusCodes
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.ToXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StatusCodes.StatusCodes


module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginGroupFailoverCriteria

-- | A complex data type that includes information about the failover
--   criteria for an origin group, including the status codes for which
--   CloudFront will failover from the primary origin to the second origin.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOriginGroupFailoverCriteria</a> smart constructor.
data OriginGroupFailoverCriteria
OriginGroupFailoverCriteria' :: StatusCodes -> OriginGroupFailoverCriteria

-- | The status codes that, when returned from the primary origin, will
--   trigger CloudFront to failover to the second origin.
[$sel:statusCodes:OriginGroupFailoverCriteria'] :: OriginGroupFailoverCriteria -> StatusCodes

-- | Create a value of <a>OriginGroupFailoverCriteria</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--

--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   <a>$sel:statusCodes:OriginGroupFailoverCriteria'</a>,
--   <a>originGroupFailoverCriteria_statusCodes</a> - The status codes
--   that, when returned from the primary origin, will trigger CloudFront
--   to failover to the second origin.
newOriginGroupFailoverCriteria :: StatusCodes -> OriginGroupFailoverCriteria

-- | The status codes that, when returned from the primary origin, will
--   trigger CloudFront to failover to the second origin.
originGroupFailoverCriteria_statusCodes :: Lens' OriginGroupFailoverCriteria StatusCodes

module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginGroup

-- | An origin group includes two origins (a primary origin and a second
--   origin to failover to) and a failover criteria that you specify. You
--   create an origin group to support origin failover in CloudFront. When
--   you create or update a distribution, you can specifiy the origin group
--   instead of a single origin, and CloudFront will failover from the
--   primary origin to the second origin under the failover conditions that
--   you've chosen.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOriginGroup</a> smart constructor.
data OriginGroup
OriginGroup' :: Text -> OriginGroupFailoverCriteria -> OriginGroupMembers -> OriginGroup

-- | The origin group's ID.
[$sel:id:OriginGroup'] :: OriginGroup -> Text

-- | A complex type that contains information about the failover criteria
--   for an origin group.
[$sel:failoverCriteria:OriginGroup'] :: OriginGroup -> OriginGroupFailoverCriteria

-- | A complex type that contains information about the origins in an
--   origin group.
[$sel:members:OriginGroup'] :: OriginGroup -> OriginGroupMembers

-- | Create a value of <a>OriginGroup</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:id:OriginGroup'</a>, <a>originGroup_id</a> - The origin
--   group's ID.
--   
--   <a>$sel:failoverCriteria:OriginGroup'</a>,
--   <a>originGroup_failoverCriteria</a> - A complex type that contains
--   information about the failover criteria for an origin group.
--   
--   <a>$sel:members:OriginGroup'</a>, <a>originGroup_members</a> - A
--   complex type that contains information about the origins in an origin
--   group.
newOriginGroup :: Text -> OriginGroupFailoverCriteria -> OriginGroupMembers -> OriginGroup

-- | The origin group's ID.
originGroup_id :: Lens' OriginGroup Text

-- | A complex type that contains information about the failover criteria
--   for an origin group.
originGroup_failoverCriteria :: Lens' OriginGroup OriginGroupFailoverCriteria

-- | A complex type that contains information about the origins in an
--   origin group.
originGroup_members :: Lens' OriginGroup OriginGroupMembers
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginGroup.OriginGroup
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginGroup.OriginGroup
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginGroup.OriginGroup
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginGroup.OriginGroup
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginGroup.OriginGroup
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginGroup.OriginGroup
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginGroup.OriginGroup
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.ToXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.OriginGroup.OriginGroup

module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingLoggingConfig

-- | A complex type that controls whether access logs are written for this
--   streaming distribution.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newStreamingLoggingConfig</a> smart constructor.
data StreamingLoggingConfig
StreamingLoggingConfig' :: Bool -> Text -> Text -> StreamingLoggingConfig

-- | Specifies whether you want CloudFront to save access logs to an Amazon
--   S3 bucket. If you don't want to enable logging when you create a
--   streaming distribution or if you want to disable logging for an
--   existing streaming distribution, specify <tt>false</tt> for
--   <tt>Enabled</tt>, and specify <tt>empty Bucket</tt> and
--   <tt>Prefix</tt> elements. If you specify <tt>false</tt> for
--   <tt>Enabled</tt> but you specify values for <tt>Bucket</tt> and
--   <tt>Prefix</tt>, the values are automatically deleted.
[$sel:enabled:StreamingLoggingConfig'] :: StreamingLoggingConfig -> Bool

-- | The Amazon S3 bucket to store the access logs in, for example,
--   <tt>myawslogbucket.s3.amazonaws.com</tt>.
[$sel:bucket:StreamingLoggingConfig'] :: StreamingLoggingConfig -> Text

-- | An optional string that you want CloudFront to prefix to the access
--   log filenames for this streaming distribution, for example,
--   <tt>myprefix/</tt>. If you want to enable logging, but you don't want
--   to specify a prefix, you still must include an empty <tt>Prefix</tt>
--   element in the <tt>Logging</tt> element.
[$sel:prefix:StreamingLoggingConfig'] :: StreamingLoggingConfig -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>StreamingLoggingConfig</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:enabled:StreamingLoggingConfig'</a>,
--   <a>streamingLoggingConfig_enabled</a> - Specifies whether you want
--   CloudFront to save access logs to an Amazon S3 bucket. If you don't
--   want to enable logging when you create a streaming distribution or if
--   you want to disable logging for an existing streaming distribution,
--   specify <tt>false</tt> for <tt>Enabled</tt>, and specify <tt>empty
--   Bucket</tt> and <tt>Prefix</tt> elements. If you specify
--   <tt>false</tt> for <tt>Enabled</tt> but you specify values for
--   <tt>Bucket</tt> and <tt>Prefix</tt>, the values are automatically
--   deleted.
--   
--   <a>$sel:bucket:StreamingLoggingConfig'</a>,
--   <a>streamingLoggingConfig_bucket</a> - The Amazon S3 bucket to store
--   the access logs in, for example,
--   <tt>myawslogbucket.s3.amazonaws.com</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:prefix:StreamingLoggingConfig'</a>,
--   <a>streamingLoggingConfig_prefix</a> - An optional string that you
--   want CloudFront to prefix to the access log filenames for this
--   streaming distribution, for example, <tt>myprefix/</tt>. If you want
--   to enable logging, but you don't want to specify a prefix, you still
--   must include an empty <tt>Prefix</tt> element in the <tt>Logging</tt>
--   element.
newStreamingLoggingConfig :: Bool -> Text -> Text -> StreamingLoggingConfig

-- | Specifies whether you want CloudFront to save access logs to an Amazon
--   S3 bucket. If you don't want to enable logging when you create a
--   streaming distribution or if you want to disable logging for an
--   existing streaming distribution, specify <tt>false</tt> for
--   <tt>Enabled</tt>, and specify <tt>empty Bucket</tt> and
--   <tt>Prefix</tt> elements. If you specify <tt>false</tt> for
--   <tt>Enabled</tt> but you specify values for <tt>Bucket</tt> and
--   <tt>Prefix</tt>, the values are automatically deleted.
streamingLoggingConfig_enabled :: Lens' StreamingLoggingConfig Bool

-- | The Amazon S3 bucket to store the access logs in, for example,
--   <tt>myawslogbucket.s3.amazonaws.com</tt>.
streamingLoggingConfig_bucket :: Lens' StreamingLoggingConfig Text

-- | An optional string that you want CloudFront to prefix to the access
--   log filenames for this streaming distribution, for example,
--   <tt>myprefix/</tt>. If you want to enable logging, but you don't want
--   to specify a prefix, you still must include an empty <tt>Prefix</tt>
--   element in the <tt>Logging</tt> element.
streamingLoggingConfig_prefix :: Lens' StreamingLoggingConfig Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingLoggingConfig.StreamingLoggingConfig
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingLoggingConfig.StreamingLoggingConfig
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingLoggingConfig.StreamingLoggingConfig
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingLoggingConfig.StreamingLoggingConfig
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingLoggingConfig.StreamingLoggingConfig
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingLoggingConfig.StreamingLoggingConfig
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingLoggingConfig.StreamingLoggingConfig

module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Tag

-- | A complex type that contains <tt>Tag</tt> key and <tt>Tag</tt> value.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTag</a> smart constructor.
data Tag
Tag' :: Maybe Text -> Text -> Tag

-- | A string that contains an optional <tt>Tag</tt> value.
--   
--   The string length should be between 0 and 256 characters. Valid
--   characters include <tt>a-z</tt>, <tt>A-Z</tt>, <tt>0-9</tt>, space,
--   and the special characters <tt>_ - . : / = + @</tt>.
[$sel:value:Tag'] :: Tag -> Maybe Text

-- | A string that contains <tt>Tag</tt> key.
--   
--   The string length should be between 1 and 128 characters. Valid
--   characters include <tt>a-z</tt>, <tt>A-Z</tt>, <tt>0-9</tt>, space,
--   and the special characters <tt>_ - . : / = + @</tt>.
[$sel:key:Tag'] :: Tag -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>Tag</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:value:Tag'</a>, <a>tag_value</a> - A string that contains an
--   optional <tt>Tag</tt> value.
--   
--   The string length should be between 0 and 256 characters. Valid
--   characters include <tt>a-z</tt>, <tt>A-Z</tt>, <tt>0-9</tt>, space,
--   and the special characters <tt>_ - . : / = + @</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:key:Tag'</a>, <a>tag_key</a> - A string that contains
--   <tt>Tag</tt> key.
--   
--   The string length should be between 1 and 128 characters. Valid
--   characters include <tt>a-z</tt>, <tt>A-Z</tt>, <tt>0-9</tt>, space,
--   and the special characters <tt>_ - . : / = + @</tt>.
newTag :: Text -> Tag

-- | A string that contains an optional <tt>Tag</tt> value.
--   
--   The string length should be between 0 and 256 characters. Valid
--   characters include <tt>a-z</tt>, <tt>A-Z</tt>, <tt>0-9</tt>, space,
--   and the special characters <tt>_ - . : / = + @</tt>.
tag_value :: Lens' Tag (Maybe Text)

-- | A string that contains <tt>Tag</tt> key.
--   
--   The string length should be between 1 and 128 characters. Valid
--   characters include <tt>a-z</tt>, <tt>A-Z</tt>, <tt>0-9</tt>, space,
--   and the special characters <tt>_ - . : / = + @</tt>.
tag_key :: Lens' Tag Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Tag.Tag
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Tag.Tag
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Tag.Tag
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Tag.Tag
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Tag.Tag
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Tag.Tag
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.Tag.Tag

module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TestResult

-- | Contains the result of testing a CloudFront function with
--   <tt>TestFunction</tt>.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTestResult</a> smart constructor.
data TestResult
TestResult' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe FunctionSummary -> Maybe Text -> TestResult

-- | The amount of time that the function took to run as a percentage of
--   the maximum allowed time. For example, a compute utilization of 35
--   means that the function completed in 35% of the maximum allowed time.
[$sel:computeUtilization:TestResult'] :: TestResult -> Maybe Text

-- | Contains the log lines that the function wrote (if any) when running
--   the test.
[$sel:functionExecutionLogs:TestResult'] :: TestResult -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The event object returned by the function. For more information about
--   the structure of the event object, see <a>Event object structure</a>
--   in the <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:functionOutput:TestResult'] :: TestResult -> Maybe Text

-- | Contains configuration information and metadata about the CloudFront
--   function that was tested.
[$sel:functionSummary:TestResult'] :: TestResult -> Maybe FunctionSummary

-- | If the result of testing the function was an error, this field
--   contains the error message.
[$sel:functionErrorMessage:TestResult'] :: TestResult -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>TestResult</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:computeUtilization:TestResult'</a>,
--   <a>testResult_computeUtilization</a> - The amount of time that the
--   function took to run as a percentage of the maximum allowed time. For
--   example, a compute utilization of 35 means that the function completed
--   in 35% of the maximum allowed time.
--   
--   <a>$sel:functionExecutionLogs:TestResult'</a>,
--   <a>testResult_functionExecutionLogs</a> - Contains the log lines that
--   the function wrote (if any) when running the test.
--   
--   <a>$sel:functionOutput:TestResult'</a>,
--   <a>testResult_functionOutput</a> - The event object returned by the
--   function. For more information about the structure of the event
--   object, see <a>Event object structure</a> in the <i>Amazon CloudFront
--   Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:functionSummary:TestResult'</a>,
--   <a>testResult_functionSummary</a> - Contains configuration information
--   and metadata about the CloudFront function that was tested.
--   
--   <a>$sel:functionErrorMessage:TestResult'</a>,
--   <a>testResult_functionErrorMessage</a> - If the result of testing the
--   function was an error, this field contains the error message.
newTestResult :: TestResult

-- | The amount of time that the function took to run as a percentage of
--   the maximum allowed time. For example, a compute utilization of 35
--   means that the function completed in 35% of the maximum allowed time.
testResult_computeUtilization :: Lens' TestResult (Maybe Text)

-- | Contains the log lines that the function wrote (if any) when running
--   the test.
testResult_functionExecutionLogs :: Lens' TestResult (Maybe [Text])

-- | The event object returned by the function. For more information about
--   the structure of the event object, see <a>Event object structure</a>
--   in the <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
testResult_functionOutput :: Lens' TestResult (Maybe Text)

-- | Contains configuration information and metadata about the CloudFront
--   function that was tested.
testResult_functionSummary :: Lens' TestResult (Maybe FunctionSummary)

-- | If the result of testing the function was an error, this field
--   contains the error message.
testResult_functionErrorMessage :: Lens' TestResult (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TestResult.TestResult
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TestResult.TestResult
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TestResult.TestResult

instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TestResult.TestResult
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TestResult.TestResult


module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedKeyGroups

-- | A list of key groups whose public keys CloudFront can use to verify
--   the signatures of signed URLs and signed cookies.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTrustedKeyGroups</a> smart constructor.
data TrustedKeyGroups
TrustedKeyGroups' :: Maybe [Text] -> Bool -> Int -> TrustedKeyGroups

-- | A list of key groups identifiers.
[$sel:items:TrustedKeyGroups'] :: TrustedKeyGroups -> Maybe [Text]

-- | This field is <tt>true</tt> if any of the key groups in the list have
--   public keys that CloudFront can use to verify the signatures of signed
--   URLs and signed cookies. If not, this field is <tt>false</tt>.
[$sel:enabled:TrustedKeyGroups'] :: TrustedKeyGroups -> Bool

-- | The number of key groups in the list.
[$sel:quantity:TrustedKeyGroups'] :: TrustedKeyGroups -> Int

-- | Create a value of <a>TrustedKeyGroups</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:items:TrustedKeyGroups'</a>, <a>trustedKeyGroups_items</a> - A
--   list of key groups identifiers.
--   
--   <a>$sel:enabled:TrustedKeyGroups'</a>, <a>trustedKeyGroups_enabled</a>
--   - This field is <tt>true</tt> if any of the key groups in the list
--   have public keys that CloudFront can use to verify the signatures of
--   signed URLs and signed cookies. If not, this field is <tt>false</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:quantity:TrustedKeyGroups'</a>,
--   <a>trustedKeyGroups_quantity</a> - The number of key groups in the
--   list.
newTrustedKeyGroups :: Bool -> Int -> TrustedKeyGroups

-- | A list of key groups identifiers.
trustedKeyGroups_items :: Lens' TrustedKeyGroups (Maybe [Text])

-- | This field is <tt>true</tt> if any of the key groups in the list have
--   public keys that CloudFront can use to verify the signatures of signed
--   URLs and signed cookies. If not, this field is <tt>false</tt>.
trustedKeyGroups_enabled :: Lens' TrustedKeyGroups Bool

-- | The number of key groups in the list.
trustedKeyGroups_quantity :: Lens' TrustedKeyGroups Int
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedKeyGroups.TrustedKeyGroups
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedKeyGroups.TrustedKeyGroups
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedKeyGroups.TrustedKeyGroups
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedKeyGroups.TrustedKeyGroups
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedKeyGroups.TrustedKeyGroups
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedKeyGroups.TrustedKeyGroups
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedKeyGroups.TrustedKeyGroups
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.ToXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedKeyGroups.TrustedKeyGroups


module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedSigners

-- | A list of accounts whose public keys CloudFront can use to verify the
--   signatures of signed URLs and signed cookies.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTrustedSigners</a> smart constructor.
data TrustedSigners
TrustedSigners' :: Maybe [Text] -> Bool -> Int -> TrustedSigners

-- | A list of account identifiers.
[$sel:items:TrustedSigners'] :: TrustedSigners -> Maybe [Text]

-- | This field is <tt>true</tt> if any of the accounts have public keys
--   that CloudFront can use to verify the signatures of signed URLs and
--   signed cookies. If not, this field is <tt>false</tt>.
[$sel:enabled:TrustedSigners'] :: TrustedSigners -> Bool

-- | The number of accounts in the list.
[$sel:quantity:TrustedSigners'] :: TrustedSigners -> Int

-- | Create a value of <a>TrustedSigners</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:items:TrustedSigners'</a>, <a>trustedSigners_items</a> - A
--   list of account identifiers.
--   
--   <a>$sel:enabled:TrustedSigners'</a>, <a>trustedSigners_enabled</a> -
--   This field is <tt>true</tt> if any of the accounts have public keys
--   that CloudFront can use to verify the signatures of signed URLs and
--   signed cookies. If not, this field is <tt>false</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:quantity:TrustedSigners'</a>, <a>trustedSigners_quantity</a> -
--   The number of accounts in the list.
newTrustedSigners :: Bool -> Int -> TrustedSigners

-- | A list of account identifiers.
trustedSigners_items :: Lens' TrustedSigners (Maybe [Text])

-- | This field is <tt>true</tt> if any of the accounts have public keys
--   that CloudFront can use to verify the signatures of signed URLs and
--   signed cookies. If not, this field is <tt>false</tt>.
trustedSigners_enabled :: Lens' TrustedSigners Bool

-- | The number of accounts in the list.
trustedSigners_quantity :: Lens' TrustedSigners Int
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedSigners.TrustedSigners
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedSigners.TrustedSigners
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedSigners.TrustedSigners
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedSigners.TrustedSigners
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedSigners.TrustedSigners
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.TrustedSigners.TrustedSigners

module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingDistributionSummary

-- | A summary of the information for a CloudFront streaming distribution.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newStreamingDistributionSummary</a> smart constructor.
data StreamingDistributionSummary
StreamingDistributionSummary' :: Text -> Text -> Text -> ISO8601 -> Text -> S3Origin -> Aliases -> TrustedSigners -> Text -> PriceClass -> Bool -> StreamingDistributionSummary

-- | The identifier for the distribution, for example,
--   <tt>EDFDVBD632BHDS5</tt>.
[$sel:id:StreamingDistributionSummary'] :: StreamingDistributionSummary -> Text

-- | The ARN (Amazon Resource Name) for the streaming distribution. For
--   example:
--   <tt>arn:aws:cloudfront::123456789012:streaming-distribution/EDFDVBD632BHDS5</tt>,
--   where <tt>123456789012</tt> is your account ID.
[$sel:arn:StreamingDistributionSummary'] :: StreamingDistributionSummary -> Text

-- | Indicates the current status of the distribution. When the status is
--   <tt>Deployed</tt>, the distribution's information is fully propagated
--   throughout the Amazon CloudFront system.
[$sel:status:StreamingDistributionSummary'] :: StreamingDistributionSummary -> Text

-- | The date and time the distribution was last modified.
[$sel:lastModifiedTime:StreamingDistributionSummary'] :: StreamingDistributionSummary -> ISO8601

-- | The domain name corresponding to the distribution, for example,
--   <tt>d111111abcdef8.cloudfront.net</tt>.
[$sel:domainName:StreamingDistributionSummary'] :: StreamingDistributionSummary -> Text

-- | A complex type that contains information about the Amazon S3 bucket
--   from which you want CloudFront to get your media files for
--   distribution.
[$sel:s3Origin:StreamingDistributionSummary'] :: StreamingDistributionSummary -> S3Origin

-- | A complex type that contains information about CNAMEs (alternate
--   domain names), if any, for this streaming distribution.
[$sel:aliases:StreamingDistributionSummary'] :: StreamingDistributionSummary -> Aliases

-- | A complex type that specifies the accounts, if any, that you want to
--   allow to create signed URLs for private content. If you want to
--   require signed URLs in requests for objects in the target origin that
--   match the <tt>PathPattern</tt> for this cache behavior, specify
--   <tt>true</tt> for <tt>Enabled</tt>, and specify the applicable values
--   for <tt>Quantity</tt> and <tt>Items</tt>.If you don't want to require
--   signed URLs in requests for objects that match <tt>PathPattern</tt>,
--   specify <tt>false</tt> for <tt>Enabled</tt> and <tt>0</tt> for
--   <tt>Quantity</tt>. Omit <tt>Items</tt>. To add, change, or remove one
--   or more trusted signers, change <tt>Enabled</tt> to <tt>true</tt> (if
--   it's currently <tt>false</tt>), change <tt>Quantity</tt> as
--   applicable, and specify all of the trusted signers that you want to
--   include in the updated distribution.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Serving Private Content through
--   CloudFront</a> in the <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:trustedSigners:StreamingDistributionSummary'] :: StreamingDistributionSummary -> TrustedSigners

-- | The comment originally specified when this distribution was created.
[$sel:comment:StreamingDistributionSummary'] :: StreamingDistributionSummary -> Text

-- | A complex type that contains information about price class for this
--   streaming distribution.
[$sel:priceClass:StreamingDistributionSummary'] :: StreamingDistributionSummary -> PriceClass

-- | Whether the distribution is enabled to accept end user requests for
--   content.
[$sel:enabled:StreamingDistributionSummary'] :: StreamingDistributionSummary -> Bool

-- | Create a value of <a>StreamingDistributionSummary</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:id:StreamingDistributionSummary'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionSummary_id</a> - The identifier for the
--   distribution, for example, <tt>EDFDVBD632BHDS5</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:StreamingDistributionSummary'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionSummary_arn</a> - The ARN (Amazon Resource
--   Name) for the streaming distribution. For example:
--   <tt>arn:aws:cloudfront::123456789012:streaming-distribution/EDFDVBD632BHDS5</tt>,
--   where <tt>123456789012</tt> is your account ID.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:StreamingDistributionSummary'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionSummary_status</a> - Indicates the current
--   status of the distribution. When the status is <tt>Deployed</tt>, the
--   distribution's information is fully propagated throughout the Amazon
--   CloudFront system.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastModifiedTime:StreamingDistributionSummary'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionSummary_lastModifiedTime</a> - The date and
--   time the distribution was last modified.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domainName:StreamingDistributionSummary'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionSummary_domainName</a> - The domain name
--   corresponding to the distribution, for example,
--   <tt>d111111abcdef8.cloudfront.net</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:s3Origin:StreamingDistributionSummary'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionSummary_s3Origin</a> - A complex type that
--   contains information about the Amazon S3 bucket from which you want
--   CloudFront to get your media files for distribution.
--   
--   <a>$sel:aliases:StreamingDistributionSummary'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionSummary_aliases</a> - A complex type that
--   contains information about CNAMEs (alternate domain names), if any,
--   for this streaming distribution.
--   
--   <a>$sel:trustedSigners:StreamingDistributionSummary'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionSummary_trustedSigners</a> - A complex type
--   that specifies the accounts, if any, that you want to allow to create
--   signed URLs for private content. If you want to require signed URLs in
--   requests for objects in the target origin that match the
--   <tt>PathPattern</tt> for this cache behavior, specify <tt>true</tt>
--   for <tt>Enabled</tt>, and specify the applicable values for
--   <tt>Quantity</tt> and <tt>Items</tt>.If you don't want to require
--   signed URLs in requests for objects that match <tt>PathPattern</tt>,
--   specify <tt>false</tt> for <tt>Enabled</tt> and <tt>0</tt> for
--   <tt>Quantity</tt>. Omit <tt>Items</tt>. To add, change, or remove one
--   or more trusted signers, change <tt>Enabled</tt> to <tt>true</tt> (if
--   it's currently <tt>false</tt>), change <tt>Quantity</tt> as
--   applicable, and specify all of the trusted signers that you want to
--   include in the updated distribution.
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Serving Private Content through
--   CloudFront</a> in the <i>Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:comment:StreamingDistributionSummary'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionSummary_comment</a> - The comment originally
--   specified when this distribution was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:priceClass:StreamingDistributionSummary'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionSummary_priceClass</a> - A complex type that
--   contains information about price class for this streaming
--   distribution.
--   
--   <a>$sel:enabled:StreamingDistributionSummary'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionSummary_enabled</a> - Whether the distribution
--   is enabled to accept end user requests for content.
newStreamingDistributionSummary :: Text -> Text -> Text -> UTCTime -> Text -> S3Origin -> Aliases -> TrustedSigners -> Text -> PriceClass -> Bool -> StreamingDistributionSummary

-- | The identifier for the distribution, for example,
--   <tt>EDFDVBD632BHDS5</tt>.
streamingDistributionSummary_id :: Lens' StreamingDistributionSummary Text

-- | The ARN (Amazon Resource Name) for the streaming distribution. For
--   example:
--   <tt>arn:aws:cloudfront::123456789012:streaming-distribution/EDFDVBD632BHDS5</tt>,
--   where <tt>123456789012</tt> is your account ID.
streamingDistributionSummary_arn :: Lens' StreamingDistributionSummary Text

--   distribution.

--   require signed URLs in requests for objects in the target origin that

module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingDistributionList

-- | A streaming distribution list.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newStreamingDistributionList</a> smart constructor.
data StreamingDistributionList
StreamingDistributionList' :: Maybe [StreamingDistributionSummary] -> Maybe Text -> Text -> Int -> Bool -> Int -> StreamingDistributionList

-- | A complex type that contains one <tt>StreamingDistributionSummary</tt>
--   element for each distribution that was created by the current account.
[$sel:items:StreamingDistributionList'] :: StreamingDistributionList -> Maybe [StreamingDistributionSummary]

-- | If <tt>IsTruncated</tt> is <tt>true</tt>, this element is present and
--   contains the value you can use for the <tt>Marker</tt> request
--   parameter to continue listing your RTMP distributions where they left
--   off.
[$sel:nextMarker:StreamingDistributionList'] :: StreamingDistributionList -> Maybe Text

-- | The value you provided for the <tt>Marker</tt> request parameter.
[$sel:marker:StreamingDistributionList'] :: StreamingDistributionList -> Text

-- | The value you provided for the <tt>MaxItems</tt> request parameter.
[$sel:maxItems:StreamingDistributionList'] :: StreamingDistributionList -> Int

-- | A flag that indicates whether more streaming distributions remain to
--   be listed. If your results were truncated, you can make a follow-up
--   pagination request using the <tt>Marker</tt> request parameter to
--   retrieve more distributions in the list.
[$sel:isTruncated:StreamingDistributionList'] :: StreamingDistributionList -> Bool

-- | The number of streaming distributions that were created by the current
--   account.
[$sel:quantity:StreamingDistributionList'] :: StreamingDistributionList -> Int

-- | Create a value of <a>StreamingDistributionList</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:items:StreamingDistributionList'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionList_items</a> - A complex type that contains
--   one <tt>StreamingDistributionSummary</tt> element for each
--   distribution that was created by the current account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:nextMarker:StreamingDistributionList'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionList_nextMarker</a> - If <tt>IsTruncated</tt>
--   is <tt>true</tt>, this element is present and contains the value you
--   can use for the <tt>Marker</tt> request parameter to continue listing
--   your RTMP distributions where they left off.
--   
--   <a>$sel:marker:StreamingDistributionList'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionList_marker</a> - The value you provided for
--   the <tt>Marker</tt> request parameter.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxItems:StreamingDistributionList'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionList_maxItems</a> - The value you provided for
--   the <tt>MaxItems</tt> request parameter.
--   
--   <a>$sel:isTruncated:StreamingDistributionList'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionList_isTruncated</a> - A flag that indicates
--   whether more streaming distributions remain to be listed. If your
--   results were truncated, you can make a follow-up pagination request
--   using the <tt>Marker</tt> request parameter to retrieve more
--   distributions in the list.
--   
--   <a>$sel:quantity:StreamingDistributionList'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionList_quantity</a> - The number of streaming
--   distributions that were created by the current account.
newStreamingDistributionList :: Text -> Int -> Bool -> Int -> StreamingDistributionList

-- | A complex type that contains one <tt>StreamingDistributionSummary</tt>
--   element for each distribution that was created by the current account.
streamingDistributionList_items :: Lens' StreamingDistributionList (Maybe [StreamingDistributionSummary])

-- | If <tt>IsTruncated</tt> is <tt>true</tt>, this element is present and
--   contains the value you can use for the <tt>Marker</tt> request
--   parameter to continue listing your RTMP distributions where they left
--   off.
streamingDistributionList_nextMarker :: Lens' StreamingDistributionList (Maybe Text)

-- | The value you provided for the <tt>Marker</tt> request parameter.
streamingDistributionList_marker :: Lens' StreamingDistributionList Text

-- | The value you provided for the <tt>MaxItems</tt> request parameter.
streamingDistributionList_maxItems :: Lens' StreamingDistributionList Int

-- | A flag that indicates whether more streaming distributions remain to
--   be listed. If your results were truncated, you can make a follow-up
--   pagination request using the <tt>Marker</tt> request parameter to
--   retrieve more distributions in the list.
streamingDistributionList_isTruncated :: Lens' StreamingDistributionList Bool

-- | The number of streaming distributions that were created by the current
--   account.
streamingDistributionList_quantity :: Lens' StreamingDistributionList Int

module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingDistributionConfig

-- | The RTMP distribution's configuration information.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newStreamingDistributionConfig</a> smart constructor.
data StreamingDistributionConfig
StreamingDistributionConfig' :: Maybe Aliases -> Maybe PriceClass -> Maybe StreamingLoggingConfig -> Text -> S3Origin -> Text -> TrustedSigners -> Bool -> StreamingDistributionConfig

-- | A complex type that contains information about CNAMEs (alternate
--   domain names), if any, for this streaming distribution.
[$sel:aliases:StreamingDistributionConfig'] :: StreamingDistributionConfig -> Maybe Aliases

-- | A complex type that contains information about price class for this
--   streaming distribution.
[$sel:priceClass:StreamingDistributionConfig'] :: StreamingDistributionConfig -> Maybe PriceClass

-- | A complex type that controls whether access logs are written for the
--   streaming distribution.
[$sel:logging:StreamingDistributionConfig'] :: StreamingDistributionConfig -> Maybe StreamingLoggingConfig

-- | A unique value (for example, a date-time stamp) that ensures that the
--   request can't be replayed.
--   
--   If the value of <tt>CallerReference</tt> is new (regardless of the
--   content of the <tt>StreamingDistributionConfig</tt> object),
--   CloudFront creates a new distribution.
--   
--   If <tt>CallerReference</tt> is a value that you already sent in a
--   previous request to create a distribution, CloudFront returns a
--   <tt>DistributionAlreadyExists</tt> error.
[$sel:callerReference:StreamingDistributionConfig'] :: StreamingDistributionConfig -> Text

-- | A complex type that contains information about the Amazon S3 bucket
--   from which you want CloudFront to get your media files for
--   distribution.
[$sel:s3Origin:StreamingDistributionConfig'] :: StreamingDistributionConfig -> S3Origin

-- | Any comments you want to include about the streaming distribution.
[$sel:comment:StreamingDistributionConfig'] :: StreamingDistributionConfig -> Text

-- | A complex type that specifies any accounts that you want to permit to
--   create signed URLs for private content. If you want the distribution
--   to use signed URLs, include this element; if you want the distribution
--   to use public URLs, remove this element. For more information, see
--   <a>Serving Private Content through CloudFront</a> in the <i>Amazon
--   CloudFront Developer Guide</i>.
[$sel:trustedSigners:StreamingDistributionConfig'] :: StreamingDistributionConfig -> TrustedSigners

-- | Whether the streaming distribution is enabled to accept user requests
--   for content.
[$sel:enabled:StreamingDistributionConfig'] :: StreamingDistributionConfig -> Bool

-- | Create a value of <a>StreamingDistributionConfig</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:aliases:StreamingDistributionConfig'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionConfig_aliases</a> - A complex type that
--   contains information about CNAMEs (alternate domain names), if any,
--   for this streaming distribution.
--   
--   <a>$sel:priceClass:StreamingDistributionConfig'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionConfig_priceClass</a> - A complex type that
--   contains information about price class for this streaming
--   distribution.
--   
--   <a>$sel:logging:StreamingDistributionConfig'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionConfig_logging</a> - A complex type that
--   controls whether access logs are written for the streaming
--   distribution.
--   
--   <a>$sel:callerReference:StreamingDistributionConfig'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionConfig_callerReference</a> - A unique value
--   (for example, a date-time stamp) that ensures that the request can't
--   be replayed.
--   
--   If the value of <tt>CallerReference</tt> is new (regardless of the
--   content of the <tt>StreamingDistributionConfig</tt> object),
--   CloudFront creates a new distribution.
--   
--   If <tt>CallerReference</tt> is a value that you already sent in a
--   previous request to create a distribution, CloudFront returns a
--   <tt>DistributionAlreadyExists</tt> error.
--   
--   <a>$sel:s3Origin:StreamingDistributionConfig'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionConfig_s3Origin</a> - A complex type that
--   contains information about the Amazon S3 bucket from which you want
--   CloudFront to get your media files for distribution.
--   
--   <a>$sel:comment:StreamingDistributionConfig'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionConfig_comment</a> - Any comments you want to
--   include about the streaming distribution.
--   
--   <a>$sel:trustedSigners:StreamingDistributionConfig'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionConfig_trustedSigners</a> - A complex type
--   that specifies any accounts that you want to permit to create signed
--   URLs for private content. If you want the distribution to use signed
--   URLs, include this element; if you want the distribution to use public
--   URLs, remove this element. For more information, see <a>Serving
--   Private Content through CloudFront</a> in the <i>Amazon CloudFront
--   Developer Guide</i>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:enabled:StreamingDistributionConfig'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionConfig_enabled</a> - Whether the streaming
--   distribution is enabled to accept user requests for content.
newStreamingDistributionConfig :: Text -> S3Origin -> Text -> TrustedSigners -> Bool -> StreamingDistributionConfig

-- | A complex type that contains information about CNAMEs (alternate
--   domain names), if any, for this streaming distribution.
streamingDistributionConfig_aliases :: Lens' StreamingDistributionConfig (Maybe Aliases)

-- | A complex type that contains information about price class for this
--   streaming distribution.
streamingDistributionConfig_priceClass :: Lens' StreamingDistributionConfig (Maybe PriceClass)

-- | A complex type that controls whether access logs are written for the
--   streaming distribution.
streamingDistributionConfig_logging :: Lens' StreamingDistributionConfig (Maybe StreamingLoggingConfig)

-- | A unique value (for example, a date-time stamp) that ensures that the
--   request can't be replayed.
--   
--   If the value of <tt>CallerReference</tt> is new (regardless of the
--   content of the <tt>StreamingDistributionConfig</tt> object),
--   CloudFront creates a new distribution.
--   
--   If <tt>CallerReference</tt> is a value that you already sent in a
--   previous request to create a distribution, CloudFront returns a
--   <tt>DistributionAlreadyExists</tt> error.
streamingDistributionConfig_callerReference :: Lens' StreamingDistributionConfig Text

-- | A complex type that contains information about the Amazon S3 bucket

--   distribution.

--   for content.

module Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags

-- | A streaming distribution Configuration and a list of tags to be
--   associated with the streaming distribution.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newStreamingDistributionConfigWithTags</a> smart
--   constructor.
data StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags
StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags' :: StreamingDistributionConfig -> Tags -> StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags

-- | A streaming distribution Configuration.
[$sel:streamingDistributionConfig:StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags'] :: StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags -> StreamingDistributionConfig

-- | A complex type that contains zero or more <tt>Tag</tt> elements.
[$sel:tags:StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags'] :: StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags -> Tags

-- | Create a value of <a>StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   
--   <a>$sel:streamingDistributionConfig:StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionConfigWithTags_streamingDistributionConfig</a>
--   - A streaming distribution Configuration.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tags:StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags'</a>,
--   <a>streamingDistributionConfigWithTags_tags</a> - A complex type that
--   contains zero or more <tt>Tag</tt> elements.
newStreamingDistributionConfigWithTags :: StreamingDistributionConfig -> Tags -> StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags

-- | A streaming distribution Configuration.
streamingDistributionConfigWithTags_streamingDistributionConfig :: Lens' StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags StreamingDistributionConfig

-- | A complex type that contains zero or more <tt>Tag</tt> elements.
streamingDistributionConfigWithTags_tags :: Lens' StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags Tags
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags.StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags.StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags.StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.CloudFront.Types.StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags.StreamingDistributionConfigWithTags
